{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f86-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2344"},"text":"§ 2344.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Methods of payment for acquisitions and transfers by the United States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f87-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Logistics support, supplies, and services may be acquired or transferred by the United States under the authority of this subchapter on a reimbursement basis or by replacement-in-kind or exchange of supplies or services of an equal value.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f88-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f89-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" In entering into agreements with the Government of another North Atlantic Treaty Organization country or other foreign country for the acquisition or transfer of logistic support, supplies, and services on a reimbursement basis, the Secretary of Defense shall negotiate for adoption of the following pricing principles for reciprocal application:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f8a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The price charged by a supplying country for logistics support, supplies, and services specifically procured by the supplying country from its contractors for a recipient country shall be no less favorable than the price for identical items or services charged by such contractors to the armed forces of the supplying country, taking into account price differentials due to delivery schedules, points of delivery, and other similar considerations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f8b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The price charged a recipient country for supplies furnished by a supplying country from its inventory, and the price charged a recipient country for logistics support and services furnished by the officers, employees, or governmental agencies of a supplying country, shall be the same as the price charged for identical supplies, support, or services acquired by an armed force of the supplying country from such governmental sources.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f8c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" To the extent that the Secretary of Defense is unable to obtain mutual acceptance by the other country involved of the reciprocal pricing principles for reimbursable transactions set forth in paragraph (1)—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f8d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the United States may not acquire from such country any logistic support, supply, or service not governed by such reciprocal pricing principles unless the United States forces commander acquiring such support, supply, or service determines (after price analysis) that the price thereof is fair and reasonable; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f8e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" transfers by the United States to such country under this subchapter of any logistic support, supply, or service that is not governed by such reciprocal pricing principles shall be subject to the pricing provisions of the Arms Export Control Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2751"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 2751","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f8f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" To the extent that indirect costs (including charges for plant and production equipment), administrative surcharges, and contract administration costs with respect to any North Atlantic Treaty Organization country or other foreign country are not waived by operation of the reciprocal pricing principles of paragraph (1), the Secretary of Defense may, on a reciprocal basis, agree to waive such costs.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f90-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/b/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The pricing principles set forth in paragraph (2) and the waiver authority provided in paragraph (3) shall also apply to agreements with North Atlantic Treaty Organization subsidiary bodies and the United Nations Organization or any regional international organization under this subchapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f91-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" In acquiring or transferring logistics support, supplies, or services under the authority of this subchapter by exchange of supplies or services, the Secretary of Defense may not agree to or carry out the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f92-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Transfers in exchange for property the acquisition of which by the Department of Defense is prohibited by law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f93-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Transfers of source, byproduct, or special nuclear materials or any other material, article, data, or thing of value the transfer of which is subject to the Atomic Energy Act of 1954 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2011"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 2011","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f94-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2344/c/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Transfers of chemical munitions.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida9681f95-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/323/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–323, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-08-04"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1017"},"text":"94 Stat. 1017","children":[],"tail":", § 2324; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/22/s11/a/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–22, § 11(a)(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-07-10"},"text":"July 10, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/138"},"text":"95 Stat. 138","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 2344, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/145/tXIII/s1304/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–145, title XIII, § 1304(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-11-08"},"text":"Nov. 8, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/741"},"text":"99 Stat. 741","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661/dA/tXI/s1104/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661, div. A, title XI, § 1104(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3964"},"text":"100 Stat. 3964","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/dA/tIX"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, div. A, title IX","children":[],"tail":", §§ 931(e)(1), 938(a), (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/1535"},"text":"103 Stat. 1535","children":[],"tail":", 1539; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/25/tVII/s701/f/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–25, title VII, § 701(f)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-04-06"},"text":"Apr. 6, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/115"},"text":"105 Stat. 115","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXIII/s1317/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XIII, § 1317(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2900"},"text":"108 Stat. 2900","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163/dA/tXII/s1204"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163, div. A, title XII, § 1204","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-06"},"text":"Jan. 6, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/3456"},"text":"119 Stat. 3456","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida9681f96-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida9681f97-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"ida9681f98-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Arms Export Control Act, referred to in subsec. (b)(2)(B), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/90/629"},"text":"Pub. L. 90–629","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1968-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1968","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/82/1320"},"text":"82 Stat. 1320","children":[],"tail":", as amended, which is classified principally to chapter 39 (§ 2751 et seq.) of Title 22, Foreign Relations and Intercourse. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2751"},"text":"section 2751 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Atomic Energy Act of 1954, referred to in subsec. (c)(2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-01/ch724"},"text":"act Aug. 1, 1946, ch. 724","children":[],"tail":", as added by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-08-30/ch1073/s1"},"text":"act Aug. 30, 1954, ch. 1073, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/919"},"text":"68 Stat. 919","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 23 (§ 2011 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2011"},"text":"section 2011 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida96a6989-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Subsec. (b)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/163"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–163","children":[],"tail":" struck out “of which the United States is a member” before “under this subchapter”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (b)(4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" inserted “and the United Nations Organization or any regional international organization of which the United States is a member” after “subsidiary bodies”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1991—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/25"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–25","children":[],"tail":" substituted “subchapter” for “chapter” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189","children":[],"tail":", §§ 931(e)(1), 938(a), substituted “equal value” for “identical or substantially identical nature” and “this subchapter” for “this chapter”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2)(B), (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s931/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 931(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “this subchapter” for “this chapter”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/189/s938/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–189, § 938(b)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (b)(1), (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661","children":[],"tail":" inserted “or other foreign country” after “country”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1985—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/145"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–145","children":[],"tail":" renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2324"},"text":"section 2324 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—Subsec. (b)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/22"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–22","children":[],"tail":" substituted “this chapter” for “this Act”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida96a698a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida96a698b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":" applicable with regard to any acquisition or transfer of logistic support, supplies, and services under authority of this subchapter that is initiated after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/s1317/j"},"text":"section 1317(j) of Pub. L. 103–337","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2341"},"text":"section 2341 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
